title: Siskiyou County Football Players of the Week
text: Siskiyou County Football Players of the Week Comment By Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com   By Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 1:07 PM Updated at 5:59 PM By Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 1:07 PM Updated at 5:59 PM SISKIYOU COUNTY Below are the Siskiyou Daily News selections for the top Siskiyou County football players for week eight of the season. * Sophomore Elisha Reyes of Mount Shasta was one of several players on the Bears who had a huge night in a 40-7 home win against Burney on Friday. It was the first win of the year for Mount Shasta, Reyes finished with 52 receiving yards and had a 30-yard TD catch. He also finished with 49 rushing yards. * Junior Tyler Santi of Mount Shasta rushed for 103 yards and a touchdown and had 14 total tackles on defense against Burney. * Junior Alex Urbano of Mount Shasta rushed for 132 yards and a touchdown vs. Burney. * Michael Benton-Ferguson of College of the Siskiyous had a huge night at wide receiver in a 49-31 road loss to American River onSaturday. He finished with 318 yards and two touchdowns on 10 catches for COS. * Quarterback Hamilton Mateski of COS also had a very strong game and threw for 320 yards with three touchdowns and two interceptions vs. American River. Mateski started the year at tight end but moved to QB when the other two signal callers for the Eagles were injured. * SeniorKirby Kindley of Mount Shasta threw for a touchdown and ran in another score against Burney. * Drew Kannely-Robles of Yreka High ran for 79 yards and two touchdowns in a loss to Anderson at home on Friday. He did not see time at running back until late in the second quarter due to an injury suffered the week before against Lassen. *Senior Camron Williams of Tulelake ran for110 yards and two touchdowns in a 36-22 home victory against Dunsmuir onFriday night. He also had an interception on defense. * Travis Hall of COS had nine total tackles and an interception vs. AmericanRiver. * Sophomore Andrew Sanders of Tulelake threw for two touchdowns in his two completions of the night in the win vs. Dunsmuir. He also had 14 total tackles on defense. * Yreka High senior Bradley Betts had five solo and 12 total tackles vs. Anderson. * Yreka High senior Garrett Plucker had four solo and 13 total tackles vs. Anderson. By Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com   By Daily News Sports Editor Bill Choybchoy@siskiyoudaily.com Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 1:07 PM Updated at 5:59 PM
